SIMPLE: hilary_term
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hilary term
<hw>Hil"a*ry term`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Formerly, one of the four
terms of the courts of common law in England, beginning on the eleventh
of January and ending on the thirty-first of the same month, in each
year; -- so called from the festival of St. Hilary, January
13th.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The Hilary term is superseded by the Hilary sittings,
which commence on the eleventh of January and end on the Wednesday
before Easter.</note> <rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hilding</ent>⟦br⟧
